{
  "texts": [
    "It is evaluated specifically on the CoderEval dataset, where test cases and test scripts are provided.",
    "V. RESULTS AND ANALYSES A. RQ1: Similarity-based EffectivenessThe evaluation results of similarity-based metrics are presented in Table II.",
    "When comparing the performance of TOOLGEN's variants and the three different base models, namely CodeGPT, CodeT5, and CodeLlama, we observe that TOOLGEN achieves similarity scores comparable to the baselines.To provide a detailed breakdown, when utilizing CodeGPT as the base model, TOOLGEN-gpt demonstrates a 2.7% improvement in BLEU-4 and a 11.9% improvement in Exact Match compared to VANILLA-gpt.",
    "However, it exhibits a 1.0% decrease in CodeBLEU and a 1.1% decrease in Edit Similarity.",
    "With the base model CodeT5, TOOLGEN-t5 exhibits 6.2%, 1.4%, and 27.9% enhancements in BLEU-4, CodeBLEU, and Exact Match relative to VANILLA-t5 but experiences a 3.1% decrease in Edit Similarity."
  ]
}